---
title: Dukkah-Crusted Chicken with Sweet Potatoes and Snap Peas
description: Dukkah (pronounced DOO-kah) is a great way to bring the crunch. The Egyptian blend of crushed nuts, spices, and seeds is fine enough to sprinkle on like a seasoning, but it also has enough rugged texture to keep it satisfyingly crisp. Here, it’s used two ways: to add a coating to butterflied chicken breasts and to bring an extra dash of flavor to roasted sweet potatoes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/uk-pan-fried-chicken-w07-3144fb7e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/uk-pan-fried-chicken-w07-14017829.pdf
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 510 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 47 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 260 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: African
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/dukkah-crusted-chicken-586bdc8b4348d26320385422
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Peel and cut @sweet potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with half the @dukkah{2%tablespoon}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until sweet potatoes are tender and dukkah is golden brown, ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

> Dukkah is an Egyptian blend of crushed nuts, spices, and seeds. It adds a crunchy coating and extra flavor.

Zest and halve @lime{2}. In a #small bowl{}, mix @sour cream{8%tablespoon}, a pinch of lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in 1 tsp water to thin.

> Add a splash more water if crema still seems thick—it should have a drizzly, saucy consistency.

Season @chicken breasts{24%ounce} all over with salt, pepper, and remaining dukkah.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and sear until dukkah is lightly browned but not burnt, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and transfer to a baking sheet. Roast in oven until no longer pink, ~{5-7%minutes}. Set aside to rest.

While chicken roasts, heat another large drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add @sugar snap peas{12%ounce} and toss until tender and lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide sweet potatoes between plates, then top with chicken and snap peas. Drizzle with citrus crema and serve.